cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.CE 

The paper deals with the risk of cascading blackouts in power systems, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and network engineering (cs.NE). The use of copula analysis to quantify the impact of correlation of initiating outages is a statistical method, which falls under data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the development of new approaches for bounding an estimate of the total number of blackout-causing contingencies, which is related to power flow analysis (cs.PF) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
